    "created_at": "2025-05-23T16:01:09Z",
    "updated_at": "2025-05-23T16:01:09Z",
    "body": "in https://pixi.sh/latest/integration/third_party/starship/ you can see a workaround for this:\n\n```toml\n[python]\n# customize python binary path for pixi\npython_binary = [\n  # this is the python from PATH if in a pixi shell\n  # (assuming you don't have python on your global PATH)\n  \"python\",\n  # fall back to pixi's python if it's available\n  \".pixi/envs/default/bin/python\",\n]\n```\n\ni don't think this is something that starship needs to fix",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
